er?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Prime Minister       Share       rose—     Share                    The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Speaker       Share       Order. There is far too much noise in the Chamber. We have heard the question, but I want to hear the Prime Minister’s answer.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Prime Minister       Share       I join the hon. Gentleman in wishing everybody a happy Christmas. I will of course have an opportunity to do that again on Monday, when I am sure the House will be as full for the statement on the European Council meeting. [Hon. Members: “Hear, hear.”] Funny, that seemed to come from this side of the House but not from the Labour side. I have to say that the Foreign Secretary is doing an absolutely excellent job. He is, in short, an FFS—a fine Foreign Secretary.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Amanda Milling (Cannock Chase) (Con)       Share       Q4. Rugeley has a really bright future ahead— [ Interruption. ]  [907703]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Speaker       Share       Order. I want to hear the voice of Cannock Chase.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Amanda Milling       Share       Rugeley has a really bright future ahead, but only if we are ambitious